1
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:54,471
EPISODE 10

2
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:00,977
They said they'd soon be back with Ha-ni.
What's taking them so long?

3
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:04,522
My goodness.

4
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:07,067
Why on earth would this fall?

5
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:15,533
Hello?

6
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:20,080
What?

7
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:21,623
No way…

8
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:27,378
Ok-jeong, what did you just say?

9
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:30,423
Stop crying and say that again.

10
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:33,551
What did you just say?

11
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:36,846
What happened to Gi-tae?

12
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:41,935
Stop crying and tell me!

13
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:04,791
Grandma.

14
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:17,053
Is it you, my puppy?

15
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,068
Ha-ni.

16
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:34,529
My sweet little puppy.

17
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:38,449
Grandma.

18
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:40,869
Do you recognize me?

19
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:47,625
How did you make it
all the way here alone?

20
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,838
You have no idea how worried I was

21
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,716
when I heard you were sick.

22
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,551
Goodness.

23
00:02:56,634 --> 00:03:00,388
What a long trip you've made.

24
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:02,932
Hardly. I took the bus.

25
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:08,021
You know, I had something to give you.

26
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:09,480
I'm glad you're here.

27
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:21,284
Keep this with you always.

28
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,703
It's the only way you'll live.

29
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:24,954
What is this?

30
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:28,499
And what do you mean I'll live?

31
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:33,004
You must answer the phone.

32
00:03:33,838 --> 00:03:36,841
No matter what, you must answer that call.

33
00:03:41,846 --> 00:03:43,056
Grandma…

34
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:45,934
I guess you're really unwell.

35
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:52,732
What on earth happened
to the great Lee Hong-nyeon?

36
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,485
My puppy.

37
00:03:55,568 --> 00:03:59,822
I'll make sure you survive.

38
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,116
I'll make sure you do.

39
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,805
-How did you get in here?
-Gosh!

40
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,767
Wait. Were you home all this time?

41
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:30,353
What's that in your hand?

42
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:33,439
Are you here to steal from us again?

43
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:35,984
Of course not. Grandma gave this to me.

44
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,945
-You know my great grandmother?
-That's none of your business.

45
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:42,031
Anyway, I'm busy, so maybe next time.

46
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:45,743
Can I have your phone number?

47
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:47,036
Why do you want it?

48
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,124
I haven't been able
to focus on my studies.

49
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:55,670
All I can think about is you.
It's driving me crazy.

50
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:57,380
What?

51
00:04:58,506 --> 00:05:01,050
Seriously? Pull yourself together!

52
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:03,511
-Do you even know who I am?
-Who are you?

53
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:04,637
Ha-ni?

54
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:14,439
My goodness.

55
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:16,607
My gosh. No way.

56
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:21,112
How can you look exactly the same
as Ha-ni back in high school?

57
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:23,656
-Goodness.
-No, you're mistaken.

58
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,034
Wait. Hold on a second.

59
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,618
I'm sorry!

60
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:31,831
My gosh. Who is that girl?

61
00:05:32,623 --> 00:05:33,916
Seong-u, do you know her?

62
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,295
She's the daughter of
Aunt Ha-ni's friend of a friend.

63
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:39,213
That's what I heard.

64
00:05:39,964 --> 00:05:41,132
The daughter of

65
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:43,593
Ha-ni's friend of a friend?

66
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,518
Wait, this belongs to Mother.

67
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:13,664
Mom, I'm sorry.

68
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:18,544
I wanted to stay and be with you more.

69
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:22,965
But I'm sorry.

70
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,725
Thanks to the changed ingredients,

71
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:36,104
Joa Strawberry has been
receiving good reviews.

72
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:40,108
And people are enjoying it
regardless of gender and age.

73
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:43,736
The power of one's palate
never ceases to amaze me.

74
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:47,198
Consumers are quick to catch
the slightest change to the taste.

75
00:06:47,281 --> 00:06:48,616
That's why…

76
00:06:49,742 --> 00:06:51,202
I'm making sure that

77
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:53,830
my world-class palate
stays at the top of its game.

78
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:55,081
This isn't for free.

79
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,502
Unbelievable.
Draw that tongue of yours back in.

80
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:02,421
-I see the white coating on it.
-White coating?

81
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:05,049
I make myself nearly vomit to clean it,
you know.

82
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:07,051
-No, I don't know.
-Why not?

83
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:10,972
Them arguing tells us
it's time to end the meeting.

84
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:13,224
You're right. That'll be all for today.

85
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:14,934
-Good job, everyone.
-Good job.

86
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:16,769
-What?
-Did you hit me?

87
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:18,146
-So what?
-Unbelievable.

88
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,522
"So what?"

89
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:21,065
You're unbelievable.

90
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,944
Hold on a second. Gosh.

91
00:07:27,738 --> 00:07:30,658
There's no need to worry.
They're just putting on a show.

92
00:07:31,325 --> 00:07:34,287
-Sorry?
-It's obvious that they're dating.

93
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,913
Maybe they want us to know now.

94
00:07:35,997 --> 00:07:37,457
Did you know?

95
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:41,043
Only they don't know that
they're the company's official couple.

96
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,712
Unbelievable.

97
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,088
Fools, right?

98
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:52,221
How do you do this kind of research?

99
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:56,309
You gather a group of consumers
online or through social media

100
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:59,103
and collect the data
from the survey they fill out.

101
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:03,316
For renewed products like Joa Strawberry
or newly-launched products,

102
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,860
the opinions of various consumers

103
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:08,863
are the most objective data
we can depend on.

104
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:11,157
The opinions of consumers.

105
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,701
That's right.

106
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,953
It's lunchtime, so let's get going.

107
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,541
Ha-ni and I will head out first,

108
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,710
so join us after five minutes.

109
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:24,170
-Got it, honey?
-Got it.

110
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:27,465
I don't think there's any need for this.

111
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:30,718
Still, it's better to be cautious
at the office.

112
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,721
It's how we've kept our secret.

113
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,558
Right.

114
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:40,061
That reminds me.

115
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:42,647
Are you dating someone at work too?

116
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:45,691
It'll be fun to go on
a double date sometime.

117
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:47,485
A double date?

118
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:51,072
That handsome cook at the cafeteria.

119
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:52,490
Isn't he your boyfriend?

120
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:55,785
No way. It's not what you think.

121
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:59,413
Don't lie to me.
He even made tteokbokki for you back then.

122
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:00,623
It's not like that.

123
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:03,251
I have to take this.

124
00:09:04,168 --> 00:09:06,045
You're just trying to change the subject.

125
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:09,340
Mom?

126
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:12,885
I'll be stopping
by your house this evening.

127
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:15,680
My house? Why?

128
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:17,723
Is something up?

129
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:20,643
I should say it in person,
so I'll see you then. Bye.

130
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:31,404
-Why on earth do you have this?
-Mother?

131
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:35,157
I gave it to Ha-ni, so why do you have it?

132
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,369
-Ha-ni?
-Give it back to her right away.

133
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:40,162
She'll die if you don't.

134
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:43,207
-Mother, please.
-Right now!

135
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:46,210
Anthony, will you go home now?

136
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:49,213
Since we're here, let's get a bite to eat.

137
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:51,215
You used to live around here.

138
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:53,259
Isn't there some place nice?

139
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:56,804
Yes, Mom's Snacks. It's great.

140
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,222
My mouth is already watering.

141
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,475
I don't see Mom's Snacks.

142
00:10:02,476 --> 00:10:04,437
It must have gone out of business.

143
00:10:05,062 --> 00:10:06,522
It must have meant a lot to you.

144
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:11,110
I always went there after skipping class.

145
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,905
I had my first kiss nearby too.

146
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,200
Your first kiss?
With that first love of yours?

147
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,301
Even the school has changed a lot.

148
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:47,063
Ha-ni.

149
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,106
Ha-ni…

150
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:11,504
Ha-ni…

151
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:21,806
Dad.

152
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:31,816
Dad…

153
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:35,528
No!

154
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:47,164
Dad…

155
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:49,333
-My gosh.
-Dad…

156
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:52,420
Dad!

157
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,880
I'm sorry, Ha-ni.

158
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:57,216
It's all my fault.

159
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,927
Dad… No! Please…

160
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:01,762
Please…

161
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:12,148
What's on your mind?

162
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:14,358
Past memories.

163
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:19,864
Has reuniting with your first love
stirred up emotions inside?

164
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,742
Is that what it is?

165
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:26,787
It could also be guilt.

166
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:28,789
Guilt? For what?

167
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,710
The reason she changed…

168
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,505
Well, it could be my fault.

169
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:37,756
What do you mean by that?

170
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:41,427
The death of Ha-ni's father.

171
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:46,056
I'm partially at fault.

172
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,350
What?

173
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:50,936
We should go, Jeong-man.

174
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:13,250
Did you throw
all the salt we have in here?

175
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,503
This could elevate
someone's blood pressure.

176
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:16,837
I won't

177
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:19,340
let it happen again.

178
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:22,676
Newbie, you'd better watch it.

179
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:25,804
We have our eyes on you at all times.

180
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,237
-Please enjoy.
-Thank you.

181
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,534
Here you go.

182
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,788
Hey, Mr. Competent.

183
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:54,667
Do you know how I can
appease the ladies' anger?

184
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:57,878
I'm too scared to even talk to them.

185
00:13:57,962 --> 00:14:01,257
This is because
I disbanded Hanwoo Galbi, right?

186
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:14,103
-Wait. This isn't what I usually drink.
-How is it?

187
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:17,856
I tried selecting
the best coffee for you today.

188
00:14:21,735 --> 00:14:23,612
Dark roast coffee. How smooth.

189
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,614
I taste the heaviness on my tongue.

190
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,032
The aftertaste is rich too.

191
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,577
Nice choice!

192
00:14:30,744 --> 00:14:34,999
Unbelievable. The way you describe
the taste of your coffee

193
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,166
is so artistic.

194
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,084
Right.

195
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:41,213
Wait. I shouldn't enjoy this on my own.

196
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:44,425
Order two more to-go
for the ladies at the kitchen.

197
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:45,676
Sure thing.

198
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:55,811
-Hello?
-Newbie.

199
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:59,315
Where have you gone
to slack off this time?

200
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:01,317
Slack off?

201
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:04,486
I'm here fetching
the most delicious coffee for you.

202
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,739
Cut the excuses and get back to work!

203
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:08,991
Yes, ma'am.

204
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:17,166
How bitter.

205
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,010
You don't like it here too?

206
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,848
I'm sorry for being so picky.

207
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,477
It's not you, but the little one inside.

208
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,980
Aren't you craving anything?

209
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:47,071
-There is this one thing.
-What is it?

210
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:52,242
I'd like some twisted breadsticks
from Granny's.

211
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,829
Let's go then. I'll buy loads of it.

212
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:59,583
We can leave right after
I'm back from the restroom.

213
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:04,713
Sure.

214
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,514
-Mom?
-Oh, hey.

215
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,934
-What brings you here?
-For lunch.

216
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,979
-Who did you come with?
-I'm here for lunch too.

217
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:20,980
Get going then.

218
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:45,587
Okay. Let's get going.

219
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,214
Thanks, honey.

220
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:00,102
You know, I saw that guy just now.

221
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,603
-Who?
-Well…

222
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:03,981
Pocheon Factory's head manager.

223
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:05,774
-The head manager?
-Yes.

224
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:08,360
I wonder why he's here.

225
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:19,663
What do you think? Can you do it?

226
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:23,292
But wouldn't that

227
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,462
do considerable damage to the company?

228
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,549
That's what I want.

229
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:35,804
It's time you work at the headquarters.

230
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:38,182
By the way,

231
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:40,893
I heard your daughter is
about to graduate college.

232
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,104
It's hard to get a job these days.

233
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:47,024
You must be extremely worried about her.

234
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,735
Well, yes.

235
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,283
Take your time
and think about it over lunch.

236
00:17:57,117 --> 00:17:58,202
I'll call you again.

237
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:14,218
I had a strange feeling about this.

238
00:18:16,678 --> 00:18:18,639
I'm glad I recorded the conversation.

239
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:22,142
But seriously,

240
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:26,396
what is Ms. Han trying to do?

241
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:35,364
Hey, what are you doing? Pack your stuff.

242
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,448
Why?

243
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:40,077
Didn't you get my text?
Mom's on her way here.

244
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:43,247
What? Why all of a sudden?

245
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,791
I don't know.
I'll call you once she leaves.

246
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:47,960
-Wait outside.
-Okay.

247
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:50,254
My gosh, seriously.

248
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:52,381
Just put them in here.

249
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:02,307
Mom, I live up there.

250
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:08,981
Your place is nice and tidy.

251
00:19:09,731 --> 00:19:10,774
Here.

252
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,777
Let me give you something to drink.

253
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,904
No, it's okay. Come sit down.

254
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,116
Goodness, this sitting mat…

255
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:22,953
What's the matter?

256
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:27,374
Earlier at Ha-yeong's place,
I saw a girl who looked just like you.

257
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:30,419
What?

258
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:33,630
She ran away,
so I didn't get a closer look,

259
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:37,009
but she looked so much like you.

260
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:39,511
Seong-u told me
she's your friend's daughter.

261
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:40,637
Who is that girl?

262
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,890
Well, she's…

263
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:44,474
my friend's daughter.

264
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:47,728
Everyone says we look alike,

265
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,563
but it's because
you didn't get a good look.

266
00:19:49,646 --> 00:19:52,649
She doesn't look like me at all.

267
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,276
Really?

268
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:57,279
But why was she at Ha-yeong's?

269
00:19:58,405 --> 00:20:00,782
She met Seong-u once.

270
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:02,534
Where is she now?

271
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:05,662
She went to the States
with my friend today.

272
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:10,167
Maybe she went there
to say goodbye to Seong-u.

273
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:12,336
Is that true?

274
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:14,880
Of course. Why would I lie about that?

275
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:19,051
Did you come here to ask me that?

276
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:22,971
No, I wanted to see how you were doing.

277
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:28,435
And your grandma wanted me
to give you this.

278
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:30,062
This?

279
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:34,733
It's my old cell phone charger.

280
00:20:34,816 --> 00:20:36,526
Why did she want me to have this?

281
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:39,905
I brought it because she made a fuss
saying you needed to have it.

282
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:42,658
You can keep it or throw it away.

283
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:47,496
I should go now.

284
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:50,624
You're leaving already?

285
00:20:50,707 --> 00:20:53,794
Ha-yeong can't take care of your grandma
all by herself. I should go.

286
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:56,964
-Mom.
-Go on inside.

287
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:57,965
Let me…

288
00:20:58,966 --> 00:20:59,841
Yu-hyeon.

289
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:03,387
-What brings you here?
-Who is he?

290
00:21:03,971 --> 00:21:06,139
Oh, she's my mom.

291
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:07,182
Oh, I see.

292
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:09,601
Hello, I'm Han Yu-hyeon.

293
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:10,769
I'm her work colleague.

294
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:14,189
A work colleague? Is that all?

295
00:21:14,982 --> 00:21:16,066
What?

296
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:21,530
I mean, it's weird that you're here
at such a late hour.

297
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:25,492
Oh, I'm sorry.
I needed to discuss something about work.

298
00:21:25,575 --> 00:21:27,452
-I'll come back next time.
-Okay.

299
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:30,247
No, I was just about to leave.

300
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,582
You can stay and discuss whatever.

301
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,167
-Mom.
-Just stay.

302
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:36,169
Yu-hyeon, I'll be right back.

303
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:37,629
-Bye, ma'am.
-Just stay.

304
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:39,006
Gosh, Mom.

305
00:21:40,173 --> 00:21:42,384
Hey, did you…

306
00:21:43,593 --> 00:21:45,595
wanted to move out because of him?

307
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:47,973
Gosh, no.

308
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:50,559
I like him.

309
00:21:50,642 --> 00:21:54,271
He's handsome, tall, and polite.

310
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:57,357
It's not what you think.

311
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:00,861
I'm saying he seems like a catch.

312
00:22:00,944 --> 00:22:02,487
You should go back inside.

313
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:09,077
-Ha-ni.
-Yes?

314
00:22:11,371 --> 00:22:13,999
I'm grateful that you're doing well.

315
00:22:19,212 --> 00:22:22,049
It's cold. You should go. Go on.

316
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:01,713
After you suggested using tofu,

317
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:05,217
I brought some toppings we could use.
What do you think?

318
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:07,636
I think they're nice.

319
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:10,931
But I don't think
fruit goes well with tofu.

320
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:14,559
The nuts are actually a good idea.

321
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:17,229
But can you think of anything else?

322
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,022
Anything else?

323
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:23,944
How about sesame seeds?

324
00:23:24,027 --> 00:23:25,445
My mom used to dip tofu

325
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:29,324
into beaten eggs with sesame seeds
before she fried them.

326
00:23:29,407 --> 00:23:30,784
And they were really good.

327
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:34,412
I think that'd work.
They would go well together.

328
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:37,207
Let's try making it
in the kitchen tomorrow.

329
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,209
I should go now.

330
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:46,049
By the way, is your mother a cab driver?

331
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:48,468
I saw her cab from up here.

332
00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:50,804
Yes, she's been doing it for a while.

333
00:23:51,930 --> 00:23:53,098
That's amazing.

334
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:55,892
I really like cab drivers.

335
00:23:55,976 --> 00:23:56,810
Why?

336
00:23:56,893 --> 00:24:00,814
Back when I was young,
a cab driver saved my life.

337
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,777
But where's your daughter?

338
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:10,907
Oh, right.

339
00:24:12,742 --> 00:24:13,785
It's so cold.

340
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:26,006
Is Mom gone?

341
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:30,886
Gosh, it's so cold.
I almost froze to death.

342
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:34,514
My goodness.

343
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:36,516
I told you not to go to Ha-yeong's.

344
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,685
I missed grandma so much.

345
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,939
Mom almost found out this time.

346
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:46,902
You know what? Mom said my name
as soon as she saw me.

347
00:24:47,402 --> 00:24:49,613
It's really hard to fool mom.

348
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:52,782
She may have aged,
but she's still so quick-witted.

349
00:24:53,783 --> 00:24:54,784
Did you have fun?

350
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:57,954
Anyway, I told her you went to the States.

351
00:24:58,038 --> 00:25:01,208
So from now on,
don't even go near Ha-yeong's place.

352
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:02,959
Okay, I won't.

353
00:25:03,543 --> 00:25:05,170
My gosh, you're unbelievable.

354
00:25:07,547 --> 00:25:09,674
Mom came and gave me this.

355
00:25:10,508 --> 00:25:13,595
Apparently, grandma told her
to give me this.

356
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:15,055
She said the same thing to me.

357
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:17,766
I wonder why.

358
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:20,352
Let me see.

359
00:25:22,896 --> 00:25:23,897
Okay.

360
00:25:33,114 --> 00:25:34,199
There we go.

361
00:25:36,701 --> 00:25:37,869
Does it turn on?

362
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:39,913
No, it's completely out.

363
00:25:39,996 --> 00:25:42,457
But I can't use this here anyway.

364
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:43,917
You're right.

365
00:25:45,543 --> 00:25:47,879
Anyway, I'll be really busy
starting from tomorrow.

366
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:50,590
So please don't cause any trouble
and stay put.

367
00:25:50,674 --> 00:25:51,925
Okay.

368
00:25:55,595 --> 00:25:57,681
By the way, where's Dad?

369
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:00,892
-What?
-I mean,

370
00:26:01,601 --> 00:26:04,521
I've seen Grandma, Mom, and Ha-yeong.

371
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:08,316
But I've never seen Dad.

372
00:26:10,819 --> 00:26:12,237
Dad is

373
00:26:13,363 --> 00:26:16,199
busy working in Daejeon.

374
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:19,744
Oh, I see.

375
00:26:20,537 --> 00:26:23,248
Then why don't we take a trip to Daejeon?

376
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,416
Hey!

377
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,668
I'm just kidding.

378
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:29,462
Gosh, it's freezing.

379
00:26:44,811 --> 00:26:46,604
Please look to your front.

380
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:51,776
Keep your eyes open and don't move.

381
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:54,654
The only thing we can do
is slow things down.

382
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:57,198
It's hard to expect things to get better.

383
00:26:59,492 --> 00:27:02,871
Are you saying I'll eventually go blind?

384
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:08,335
You should tell your family
before it's too late.

385
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:14,758
Not yet.

386
00:27:16,593 --> 00:27:18,970
Especially not to him.

387
00:28:12,857 --> 00:28:14,567
Goodness, I'm sorry.

388
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,321
You…

389
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:21,074
Why are you wearing sunglasses
in the middle of the night?

390
00:28:21,157 --> 00:28:21,991
Why are you here?

391
00:28:22,075 --> 00:28:24,411
I'm on my way to dinner.
I got hungry while working.

392
00:28:24,494 --> 00:28:26,162
What work? The cafeteria is closed.

393
00:28:26,246 --> 00:28:27,288
None of your business.

394
00:28:28,039 --> 00:28:28,957
I'll see you.

395
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:32,419
Do you want me

396
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:34,337
to buy you dinner?

397
00:28:45,598 --> 00:28:47,434
How do you know this place?

398
00:28:47,517 --> 00:28:49,185
Do-yun brought me here.

399
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:52,731
But why didn't you ever teach me
how to drink

400
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:54,107
like you did with Do-yun?

401
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:57,152
You were always too busy to drink with me.

402
00:28:58,403 --> 00:28:59,404
Was I?

403
00:29:01,030 --> 00:29:03,074
How's the preparation
for the contest going?

404
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:05,493
It's going okay.

405
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:06,453
It's fun.

406
00:29:08,288 --> 00:29:12,417
You used to make such a fuss
because you hated snacks.

407
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:13,793
What's gotten into you?

408
00:29:13,877 --> 00:29:15,795
It's not the snacks I hated.

409
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:17,630
I was just angry at you.

410
00:29:18,631 --> 00:29:19,716
What?

411
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:24,012
People always say
snacks remind them of the good days.

412
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:26,765
But snacks only remind me of

413
00:29:28,308 --> 00:29:30,268
how lonely I used to be.

414
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:36,858
Back then, I admit I didn't spend
a lot of time with you

415
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,526
because I was too busy with work.

416
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:41,237
It's fine. It's all in the past.

417
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:44,908
So how do you feel about snacks now?

418
00:29:47,869 --> 00:29:50,371
I'm still not that fond of them.

419
00:29:51,289 --> 00:29:52,832
But how should I put it?

420
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:55,752
I think I kind of get
why people become so happy

421
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:58,713
over a bag of snacks.

422
00:30:05,094 --> 00:30:06,888
Here. Pour me a glass.

423
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:09,015
Sure.

424
00:30:11,017 --> 00:30:13,853
Hey, one hand should hold the bottle,

425
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:17,315
and the other hand should support
your wrist or arm.

426
00:30:17,398 --> 00:30:18,858
Why does that even matter?

427
00:30:19,442 --> 00:30:22,779
This is why you need to learn
how to drink from adults. Try it.

428
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:25,865
Here.

429
00:30:28,993 --> 00:30:30,161
Hey, hey!

430
00:30:31,746 --> 00:30:33,414
You shouldn't pour too much.

431
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:36,334
Gosh, just drink it.
It's all going to go in your belly anyway.

432
00:30:46,928 --> 00:30:50,390
I can't believe
we're drinking together like this.

433
00:30:53,726 --> 00:30:55,228
-Cheers.
-Okay.

434
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:06,447
Shall we give it a try?

435
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:29,512
Press it again.

436
00:31:47,780 --> 00:31:49,365
Let's try one more time.

437
00:31:52,076 --> 00:31:53,411
Here we go.

438
00:32:19,062 --> 00:32:20,355
What do you think?

439
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:22,607
It's not bad.

440
00:32:23,316 --> 00:32:25,360
But it tastes a bit bland.

441
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:26,361
Gosh.

442
00:32:26,861 --> 00:32:28,196
Maybe it's just you.

443
00:32:28,988 --> 00:32:31,240
I'm an expert when it comes to snacks.

444
00:32:31,324 --> 00:32:35,161
I can tell if it's going to be a hit
just by tasting it.

445
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:39,624
Then why don't we test our new product?

446
00:32:39,707 --> 00:32:41,709
-Test it?
-Yes.

447
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:43,503
Tomorrow's the weekend.

448
00:32:43,586 --> 00:32:45,838
So we should go outside

449
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:48,591
and let people taste it
for the next two days.

450
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:51,094
Tomorrow?

451
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,763
I have plans tomorrow.

452
00:32:53,846 --> 00:32:56,849
Gosh, then that won't work. What a pity.

453
00:32:56,933 --> 00:32:58,267
Let's do it on Sunday.

454
00:32:58,351 --> 00:33:00,561
We can't gather enough information
in one day.

455
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:03,856
And it's hard to get feedback
from a variety of age groups.

456
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:06,109
Then…

457
00:33:06,192 --> 00:33:08,403
Why don't we ask our acquaintances?

458
00:33:08,486 --> 00:33:10,071
We have no acquaintances.

459
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:11,239
I'll take care of it.

460
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:14,450
So that means tomorrow,
we're all free to do whatever.

461
00:33:16,369 --> 00:33:17,537
Okay?

462
00:33:31,968 --> 00:33:33,219
Gosh, you startled me!

463
00:33:34,012 --> 00:33:36,139
-Gosh.
-Where are you sneaking off to?

464
00:33:36,222 --> 00:33:38,558
I'm meeting someone.

465
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:40,393
You're meeting someone?

466
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:42,478
-Who?
-What?

467
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:44,731
I'm meeting So-hye.

468
00:33:44,814 --> 00:33:47,275
Gosh, don't lie to me.

469
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:50,695
Hey, I'm you.

470
00:33:50,778 --> 00:33:52,488
I can see your eyes flickering.

471
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:55,158
-Open your bag.
-Are you my teacher or what?

472
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:57,744
Why are you checking what's in my bag?

473
00:33:57,827 --> 00:33:58,953
Three, two, one.

474
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,997
You're just like Mom.

475
00:34:01,998 --> 00:34:06,127
I didn't want to wake you
by making a sound.

476
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:09,672
I was being considerate
so you could sleep in.

477
00:34:09,756 --> 00:34:11,716
Where are you off to with this outfit?

478
00:34:11,799 --> 00:34:14,677
I felt so stuffy inside.

479
00:34:14,761 --> 00:34:18,014
So I thought I'd go for a walk.

480
00:34:22,101 --> 00:34:23,895
-What's this?
-Don't touch it.

481
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:26,230
That's mine!

482
00:34:26,314 --> 00:34:27,440
It's mine!

483
00:34:30,359 --> 00:34:32,695
"The Point Entertainment"?

484
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:42,288
MANAGEMENT CONTRACT

485
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:47,293
What is this?

486
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:49,545
Answer me!

487
00:34:52,924 --> 00:34:53,758
This one.

488
00:34:53,841 --> 00:34:55,968
-The third one.
-No, not this. This won't do.

489
00:34:56,052 --> 00:34:58,471
-Doesn't this one look too cheap?
-How about…

490
00:35:00,389 --> 00:35:02,100
Did you give her this?

491
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:05,728
-No.
-Hello, ma'am.

492
00:35:05,812 --> 00:35:07,605
We were meaning to visit you.

493
00:35:07,688 --> 00:35:09,941
We'd like to make your daughter
into a top star.

494
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:13,444
Forget it. She has neither the intentions

495
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:15,279
nor the ability to become a celebrity,

496
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:16,906
so don't give her false hope.

497
00:35:16,989 --> 00:35:19,784
I don't have the ability?
How could you say that?

498
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:22,328
These days,
kids who are impudent and rude,

499
00:35:22,411 --> 00:35:24,539
and who interfere in adults' conversation

500
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,624
are complimented for their "swag."

501
00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:28,918
The public loves them.

502
00:35:29,669 --> 00:35:31,754
-Sir.
-Chun-sik.

503
00:35:33,047 --> 00:35:34,590
No. Anthony.

504
00:35:35,508 --> 00:35:37,343
Let me ask you a favor.

505
00:35:38,302 --> 00:35:40,972
If she ever comes here again
and does something foolish,

506
00:35:42,223 --> 00:35:43,349
let me know.

507
00:35:45,685 --> 00:35:46,894
Let's go.

508
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:50,523
No. I want to watch them film
and become a celebrity too!

509
00:35:50,606 --> 00:35:52,859
-Have you gone insane?
-Goodness.

510
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:55,486
Why are you so immature and reckless?

511
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:57,697
How am I being reckless?

512
00:35:58,364 --> 00:36:01,576
Must I stay home waiting for you all day
and do as you say?

513
00:36:02,076 --> 00:36:03,452
Am I a doll or something?

514
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:07,748
That's no way to talk to your mom!

515
00:36:08,291 --> 00:36:10,668
What an impudent, little girl.

516
00:36:10,751 --> 00:36:12,920
You were worse than me at my age.

517
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,381
A dean beat you with a mop
for being cheeky.

518
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:19,051
How did you know that?

519
00:36:19,135 --> 00:36:20,386
Did you tell her?

520
00:36:21,971 --> 00:36:24,307
Yes. Let's say that I did.

521
00:36:25,808 --> 00:36:28,603
Come on out. Stop talking nonsense,
and we'll talk at home.

522
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:31,355
-I don't want to.
-What?

523
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:33,900
-Hey.
-No. Don't do that.

524
00:36:33,983 --> 00:36:35,067
-Wait.
-Hey.

525
00:36:35,151 --> 00:36:36,360
Gosh. Stop it!

526
00:36:36,444 --> 00:36:37,570
I don't want to!

527
00:36:37,653 --> 00:36:41,699
Mother, that's enough.
You know what kids are like at her age!

528
00:36:41,782 --> 00:36:43,284
"Mother"?

529
00:36:43,367 --> 00:36:46,662
Stop calling me that!
I've never been married before!

530
00:36:48,497 --> 00:36:50,041
But you had her?

531
00:36:50,124 --> 00:36:52,501
