00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:11,294
The class is in full swing.

795
00:52:11,378 --> 00:52:12,295
Let's hurry.

796
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:13,547
Okay.

797
00:52:20,512 --> 00:52:24,516
Thank you so much for making time today.

798
00:52:27,644 --> 00:52:31,231
Please try these snacks

799
00:52:31,314 --> 00:52:33,483
and fill out the questionnaire.

800
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:37,279
Your honesty is the most important,

801
00:52:37,362 --> 00:52:41,199
so please write down all the things
that the snacks lack.

802
00:52:41,283 --> 00:52:43,201
PLEASE EVALUATE YOUR SNACK OF CHOICE

803
00:52:43,285 --> 00:52:44,119
100 POINTS

804
00:52:45,787 --> 00:52:47,706
PLEASE LET US KNOW WHY
IT LACKS AN EDGE

805
00:52:51,793 --> 00:52:55,213
Did you read the ones the students wrote?

806
00:52:55,297 --> 00:52:58,508
I think they didn't like the snacks,

807
00:52:58,592 --> 00:53:00,135
but I don't get what they wrote.

808
00:53:00,218 --> 00:53:01,469
"It lacks an edge."

809
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:04,639
"I have a lot to say but CBF."

810
00:53:04,723 --> 00:53:07,183
"Not fun, cool, or sexy."

811
00:53:07,267 --> 00:53:08,518
What do they mean?

812
00:53:08,602 --> 00:53:12,022
What's wrong? I like this one.

813
00:53:12,772 --> 00:53:16,318
"That guy is sweeter than these snacks.
I'll cherish him in my heart."

814
00:53:16,401 --> 00:53:18,904
Come on. This isn't a popularity poll.

815
00:53:18,987 --> 00:53:20,030
What's with you?

816
00:53:20,614 --> 00:53:21,615
Anyway…

817
00:53:22,282 --> 00:53:26,328
Just like she said,
they must think the snacks are too boring.

818
00:53:26,411 --> 00:53:29,706
See? I told you. I know my onions
when it comes to snacks.

819
00:53:30,707 --> 00:53:33,293
It's not just the students.

820
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:37,005
Even the middle-aged ladies said
that the taste wasn't bad,

821
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:39,090
but everything about the snack
was too bland.

822
00:53:39,174 --> 00:53:41,343
The majority found the snacks boring.

823
00:53:44,888 --> 00:53:46,514
It's getting late.

824
00:53:47,515 --> 00:53:48,683
Let's resume tomorrow.

825
00:53:48,767 --> 00:53:50,435
He's right. Let's sleep first.

826
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:52,145
What time is it?

827
00:53:52,979 --> 00:53:55,982
Okay, then.
Mr. Blue Bird, you should leave.

828
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:58,777
I'm not Blue Bird. I'll get going, then.

829
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:02,072
-Okay.
-You don't need to see me out.

830
00:54:03,198 --> 00:54:05,367
-Good job today.
-You too.

831
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:07,369
Goodnight.

832
00:54:07,452 --> 00:54:09,245
Hey, kid. Goodnight.

833
00:54:09,829 --> 00:54:11,164
Goodbye.

834
00:54:31,434 --> 00:54:33,269
HYEONGJE MART

835
00:54:33,353 --> 00:54:36,106
WE ARE UP FOR A CHALLENGE

836
00:54:36,189 --> 00:54:37,691
Put that in.

837
00:54:43,029 --> 00:54:45,699
I wonder what they're up to this time.

838
00:54:45,782 --> 00:54:47,492
Who cares?

839
00:54:47,575 --> 00:54:49,577
We'll just watch them
and have puffed rice.

840
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:53,331
Every neighborhood
has a couple of eccentrics.

841
00:54:53,415 --> 00:54:55,834
They're not eccentrics.

842
00:54:55,917 --> 00:54:57,919
-They're aliens.
-"Aliens"?

843
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:05,885
Yeong-gu, this is our 372nd attempt.

844
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:08,847
No, the 373rd. We also tried
holding in our poop last time.

845
00:55:08,930 --> 00:55:11,558
You're right. Let's succeed this time!

846
00:55:11,641 --> 00:55:12,892
We must.

847
00:55:12,976 --> 00:55:17,063
We've been working on this machine
day and night for the past month.

848
00:55:17,147 --> 00:55:20,775
We'll be sending puffed rice to the moon
for the first time in history.

849
00:55:24,237 --> 00:55:26,990
-Il-gu, put it in.
-Okay!

850
00:55:27,866 --> 00:55:29,784
-They're about to do it.
-Let's see.

851
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:36,291
On the count of three…

852
00:55:37,042 --> 00:55:39,252
Hey, moon rabbit!

853
00:55:39,335 --> 00:55:42,213
Here comes the puffed rice!

854
00:55:42,297 --> 00:55:43,882
-One!
-One!

855
00:55:43,965 --> 00:55:45,008
-Two!
-Two!

856
00:55:45,592 --> 00:55:46,843
-Three!
-Three!

857
00:55:46,926 --> 00:55:48,053
-Puff!
-Puff!

858
00:55:48,136 --> 00:55:49,929
Puff!

859
00:56:21,586 --> 00:56:22,837
That's it.

860
00:56:23,922 --> 00:56:24,881
What?

861
00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:28,843
The snack we're working on.

862
00:56:30,303 --> 00:56:32,097
I've got an idea

863
00:56:33,181 --> 00:56:34,432
on how to make it.

864
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:40,021
We'll pour puffed rice

865
00:56:41,898 --> 00:56:43,358
on top of our tofu snacks.

866
00:56:45,401 --> 00:56:48,655
Other ingredients could ruin
the taste of tofu.

867
00:56:48,738 --> 00:56:51,032
But puffed rice will complement it.

868
00:56:52,033 --> 00:56:54,661
It'll also add to
the taste and the texture.

869
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:58,289
It'll make up for the snack's weakness.

870
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:14,389
It'll also bring a sense of nostalgia.

871
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:39,789
2020 JOA CONFECTIONERY
IDEA CONTEST PRESENTATION

872
00:57:44,544 --> 00:57:48,882
I've been praying for rain
every single day.

873
00:57:49,549 --> 00:57:51,634
But I'll pray for something else today.

874
00:57:51,718 --> 00:57:53,470
Please give courage

875
00:57:53,553 --> 00:57:57,682
to the 37-year-old me
so she can do well on her presentation.

876
00:58:10,737 --> 00:58:11,738
Hold on.

877
00:58:13,615 --> 00:58:15,366
That's my phone.

878
00:58:41,100 --> 00:58:42,644
Hello.

879
00:58:42,727 --> 00:58:46,523
I'm here presenting for team Star Land.
I work for the Product Development Team.

880
00:58:46,606 --> 00:58:49,317
My name is Bahn Ha-ni.

881
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:57,844
I'll change that destiny or whatever.
You can do it.

882
00:59:57,927 --> 01:00:00,096
-That little boy is Yu-hyeon?
-Yes.

883
01:00:00,179 --> 01:00:01,931
I was so surprised too.

884
01:00:02,015 --> 01:00:04,517
-Cheers!
-I don't remember anything except this.

885
01:00:04,601 --> 01:00:06,644
-What's that?
-Ha-ni's smile.

886
01:00:06,728 --> 01:00:07,645
Don't worry.

887
01:00:07,729 --> 01:00:08,771
I'll keep that promise.

888
01:00:08,855 --> 01:00:10,940
You've kept this all along?

889
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:15,486
It's time. Come here with the girl
from the past before it's too late.

890
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,822
The girl from the past?

